sentences: François Rauber (19 January 1933 – 14 December 2003) was a French pianist, composer, arranger and conductor known for his works with chansonnier Jacques Brel.
Rauber is also the composer of the Napoleonic March in the Colonel Chabert French movie by Yves Angelo.
During the 1980s and early 1990s, he worked extensively with Portuguese singer-songwriter Fernando Tordo and served as arranger and conductor in some of his records.
